rainbow conditions
==================

solar geometry, weather data and pot-of-gold locations for rainbow
photos taken in sheffield. reads EXIF from each photo to compute sun
position, antisolar point, and rainbow arc geometry.

https://ltrg.co.uk/rainbows/


how it works
------------

photos are served as AVIF at 1600px. EXIF GPS and timestamp data are
read client-side with exifr, then used to calculate sun altitude/azimuth
and the expected rainbow arc. weather data is fetched from Open-Meteo.

a daily launchd job (scan.sh) searches macOS Photos.app for rainbow
images using its built-in AI search, exports new finds, converts them
to AVIF with avifenc, updates app.js, and pushes to deploy via GitHub
Pages.


files
-----

index.html    page shell
app.js        all client logic (EXIF, sun maths, weather, gallery, map)
style.css     styles
Makefile      HEIC/PNG -> AVIF conversion (sips + avifenc)
scan.sh       daily photo scan and deploy script
photos/raw/   original exports from Photos.app (gitignored)
photos/web/   1600px AVIF web versions


dependencies
------------

avifenc       brew install libavif
sips          ships with macOS
leaflet       CDN
exifr         CDN


scan schedule
-------------

the launchd agent at ~/Library/LaunchAgents/uk.co.ltrg.rainbows.scan.plist
runs scan.sh daily at 09:00 when the user is logged in. logs go to
/tmp/rainbows-scan.log.

to exclude false positives from Photos.app search, add the filename
stem (e.g. IMG_1234) to the EXCLUDE array at the top of scan.sh.
